		 Saturday, January 25, 2003 				 Lehmann loses Yorks captaincy
																								London: Australian batsman Darren Lehmann was on Friday replaced as Yorkshire captain by Anthony McGrath, the English County opting for its third skipper in as many seasons. 																								Yorkshire have been under intense pressure to drop Lehmann because of the racial remarks he made while playing for Australia in an ODI against Sri Lanka last week. (AFP)
